$ SQL Server: datatype datetime2
@ datetime2

`datetime2` is a → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types[data type] that is able to store a date-time value with a maximum accuracy of 100 nano seconds. Thus, it extends the
data type → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/datetime[`datetime`] which is less accurate.

The range of possible values extends from `0001-01-01 00:00:00.0000000` to `9999-31-12 23:59:59.9999999`.

→ development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/functions#t-sql-sysdatetime[`sysdatetime()`] returns the current date and time as as `datetime2(7)`.

sa:

  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/datetime[`datetime`] and
  → development/databases/SQL-Server/T-SQL/data-types/_date-time[date and/or time related data types]
